events.title: CID Case Updates Meeting
events.description: A weekly classified meeting for case updates, organized by the FBI's Criminal Investigative Division (CID).

keyFacts: The FBI's Criminal Investigative Division (CID) held weekly classified case update meetings.
The meeting on March 21, 2018, was scheduled in a secure conference room (CID Large Conference Room 3853).
The calendar entry was created and modified in late 2018, indicating ongoing case management activity.
The meeting was classified as 'X-PERSONAL', suggesting sensitive or personal case matters were discussed.
This document shows structured, recurring coordination within the FBI regarding investigative cases.
